data.document: The Windows Internet Naming Service (WINS) in Windows NT Server 4.0 SP 6a, NT Terminal Server 4.0 SP 6, Windows 2000 Server SP3 and SP4, and Windows Server 2003 does not properly validate the computer name value in a WINS packet, which allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary code or cause a denial of service (server crash), which results in an "unchecked buffer" and possibly triggers a buffer overflow, aka the "Name Validation Vulnerability."

data.name: CVE-2004-0750
data.document: Unknown vulnerability in redhat-config-nfs before 1.0.13, when shares are exported to multiple hosts, can produce incorrect permissions and prevent the all_squash option from being applied.

data.name: CVE-2004-0486
data.document: HelpViewer in Mac OS X 10.3.3 and 10.2.8 processes scripts that it did not initiate, which can allow attackers to execute arbitrary code, an issue that was originally reported as a directory traversal vulnerability in the Safari web browser using the runscript parameter in a help: URI handler.

references.name: 20040516 Vuln. MacOSX/Safari: Remote help-call, execute scripts

data.name: CVE-2004-1062
data.document: Multiple cross-site scripting (XSS) vulnerabilities in ViewCVS 0.9.2 allow remote attackers to inject arbitrary HTML and web script via certain error messages.

data.name: CVE-2004-0233
data.document: Utempter allows device names that contain .. (dot dot) directory traversal sequences, which allows local users to overwrite arbitrary files via a symlink attack on device names in combination with an application that trusts the utmp or wtmp files.

data.name: CVE-2004-0136
data.document: The mapelf32exec function call in IRIX 6.5.20 through 6.5.24 allows local users to cause a denial of service (system crash) via a "corrupted binary."

data.name: CVE-2004-0204
data.document: Directory traversal vulnerability in the web viewers for Business Objects Crystal Reports 9 and 10, and Crystal Enterprise 9 or 10, as used in Visual Studio .NET 2003 and Outlook 2003 with Business Contact Manager, Microsoft Business Solutions CRM 1.2, and other products, allows remote attackers to read and delete arbitrary files via ".." sequences in the dynamicimag argument to crystalimagehandler.aspx.

references.name: 20040608 Vulnerability: Arbitrary File Access & DoS in Crystal Reports

data.name: CVE-2004-2135
data.document: cryptoloop on Linux kernel 2.6.x, when used on certain file systems with a block size 1024 or greater, has certain "IV computation" weaknesses that allow watermarked files to be detected without decryption.

references.name: [linux-kernel] 20040219 Re: Oopsing cryptoapi (or loop device?) on 2.6.*

data.name: CVE-2004-0751
data.document: The char_buffer_read function in the mod_ssl module for Apache 2.x, when using reverse proxying to an SSL server, allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (segmentation fault).

data.name: CVE-2004-0635
data.document: The SNMP dissector in Ethereal 0.8.15 through 0.10.4 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (process crash) via a (1) malformed or (2) missing community string, which causes an out-of-bounds read.

data.name: CVE-2004-0116
data.document: An Activation function in the RPCSS Service involved with DCOM activation for Microsoft Windows 2000, XP, and 2003 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (memory consumption) via an activation request with a large length field.

data.name: CVE-2004-0504
data.document: Ethereal 0.10.3 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (crash) via certain SIP messages between Hotsip servers and clients.

data.name: CVE-2004-1975
data.document: Cross-site scripting (XSS) vulnerability in the category module in pafiledb.php for paFileDB 3.1 allows remote attackers to inject arbitrary web script or HTML via the id parameter, a vulnerability that is closely related to CVE-2004-1551.

references.name: 20040925 New XSS vulnerabilities in paFileDB 3.1 final

data.name: CVE-2004-2038
data.document: Cross-site scripting (XSS) vulnerability in Land Down Under (LDU) before LDU 700 allows remote attackers to inject arbitrary web script or HTML via a BBcode img tag in (1) functions.php, (2) header.php or (3) auth.inc.php.

data.name: CVE-2004-0451
data.document: Multiple format string vulnerabilities in the (1) logquit, (2) logerr, or (3) loginfo functions in Software Upgrade Protocol (SUP) allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary code via format string specifiers in messages that are logged by syslog.

data.name: CVE-2004-0475
data.document: The showHelp function in Internet Explorer 6 on Windows XP Pro allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary local .CHM files via a double backward slash ("\\") before the target CHM file, as demonstrated using an "ms-its" URL to ntshared.chm.  NOTE: this bug may overlap CVE-2003-1041.

data.name: CVE-2004-0729
data.document: PhpBB 2.0.8 allows remote attackers to gain sensitive information via an invalid (1) category_rows parameter to index.php, (2) faq parameter to faq.php, or (3) ranksrow parameter to profile.php, which reveal the full path in an error message.

references.name: 20040716 [waraxe-2004-SA#034 - XSS and path full path disclosure in PhpBB 2.0.8]

data.name: CVE-2004-1727
data.document: BadBlue 2.5 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (refuse HTTP connections) via a large number of connections from the same IP address.

references.name: 20040820 BadBlue Webserver v2.5 Denial Of Service Vulnerability

data.name: CVE-2004-0478
data.document: Unknown versions of Mozilla allow remote attackers to cause a denial of service (high CPU/RAM consumption) using Javascript with an infinite loop  that continues to add input to a form, possibly as the result of inserting control characters, as demonstrated using an embedded ctrl-U.

references.name: [Dailydave] 20040514 Mozilla bug might even get fixed!

data.name: CVE-2004-0138
data.document: The ELF loader in Linux kernel 2.4 before 2.4.25 allows local users to cause a denial of service (crash) via a crafted ELF file with an interpreter with an invalid arch (architecture), which triggers a BUG() when an invalid VMA is unmapped.

data.name: CVE-2004-2042
data.document: Multiple SQL injection vulnerabilities in e107 0.615 allow remote attackers to inject arbitrary SQL code and gain sensitive information via (1) content parameter to content.php, (2) content_id parameter to content.php, or (3) list parameter to news.php.

data.name: CVE-2004-0521
data.document: SQL injection vulnerability in SquirrelMail before 1.4.3 RC1 allows remote attackers to execute unauthorized SQL statements, with unknown impact, probably via abook_database.php.

data.name: CVE-2004-0720
data.document: Safari 1.2.2 does not properly prevent a frame in one domain from injecting content into a frame that belongs to another domain, which facilitates web site spoofing and other attacks, aka the frame injection vulnerability.

data.name: CVE-2004-1997
data.document: Kolab stores OpenLDAP passwords in plaintext in the slapd.conf file, which may be installed world-readable, which allows local users to gain privileges.

references.name: [kolab-users] 20040420 Possible Kolab LDAP configuration information disclosure

data.name: CVE-2004-0523
data.document: Multiple buffer overflows in krb5_aname_to_localname for MIT Kerberos 5 (krb5) 1.3.3 and earlier allow remote attackers to execute arbitrary code as root.

data.name: CVE-2004-1722
data.document: SQL injection vulnerability in calendar.html in Merak Mail Server 5.2.7 allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary SQL statements via the schedule parameter.

data.name: CVE-2004-1322
data.document: Cisco Unity 2.x, 3.x, and 4.x, when integrated with Microsoft Exchange, has several hard coded usernames and passwords, which allows remote attackers to gain unauthorized access and change configuration settings or read outgoing or incoming e-mail messages.

references.name: 20041215 Cisco Unity Integrated with Exchange Has Default Passwords

data.name: CVE-2004-1377
data.document: The (1) fixps (aka fixps.in) and (2) psmandup (aka psmandup.in) scripts in a2ps before 4.13 allow local users to overwrite arbitrary files via a symlink attack on temporary files.

data.name: CVE-2004-0222
data.document: Multiple memory leaks in isakmpd in OpenBSD 3.4 and earlier allow remote attackers to cause a denial of service (memory exhaustion) via certain ISAKMP packets, as demonstrated by the Striker ISAKMP Protocol Test Suite.

references.name: 20040323 R7-0018: OpenBSD isakmpd payload handling denial-of-service vulnerabilities

data.name: CVE-2004-2039
data.document: e107 0.615 allows remote attackers to obtain sensitive information via a direct request to (1) alt_news.php, (2) backend_menu.php, (3) clock_menu.php, (4) counter_menu.php, (5) login_menu.php, and other files, which reveal the full path in a PHP error message.

data.name: CVE-2004-0703
data.document: Unknown vulnerability in the administrative controls in Bugzilla 2.17.1 through 2.17.7 allows users with "grant membership" privileges to grant memberships to groups that the user does not control.

data.name: CVE-2004-0733
data.document: Format string vulnerability in OllyDbg 1.10 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (crash) and possibly execute arbitrary code via format string specifiers that are directly provided to the OutputDebugString function call.

data.name: CVE-2004-0638
data.document: Buffer overflow in the KSDWRTB function in the dbms_system package (dbms_system.ksdwrt) for Oracle 9i Database Server Release 2 9.2.0.3 and 9.2.0.4, 9i Release 1 9.0.1.4 and 9.0.1.5, and 8i Release 1 8.1.7.4, allows remote authorized users to execute arbitrary code via a long second argument.

references.name: 20040902 Oracle Database Server dbms_system.ksdwrt Buffer Overflow Vulnerability
20040905 Buffer Overflow in DBMS_SYSTEM.KSDWRT() in Oracle8i - 9i

data.name: CVE-2004-0628
data.document: Stack-based buffer overflow in MySQL 4.1.x before 4.1.3, and 5.0, allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service (crash) and possibly execute arbitrary code via a long scramble string.

data.name: CVE-2004-0561
data.document: Format string vulnerability in the log routine for gopher daemon (gopherd) 3.0.3 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service and possibly execute arbitrary code.

data.name: CVE-2004-0205
data.document: Buffer overflow in Microsoft Internet Information Server (IIS) 4.0 allows local users to execute arbitrary code via the redirect function.
